        $$ {\Gamma^r}_{t t} $$ and $$ {\Gamma^r}_{\phi \phi} $$ both remain the same. However, we now also have to include $$ {\Gamma^r}_{t \phi} = {\Gamma^r}_{\phi t} = - \frac{L \sin^2 \theta}{r (2M + r)} $$. The geodesic equation becomes, as $$ \theta = \frac{\pi}{2} $$,

